	Bald Berry    
	 Los Angeles, Feb. 14 (PTI): Oscar-winning actress Halle Berry, who wooed audiences with her glamourous turn as the Bond girl in Die Another Day, will soon be seen as a bald woman in her next film.      
	Berry will shave her real hair to go bald for her role in the romantic comedy Nappily Ever After, reported the gossip website Ace Showbiz. Im going to shave my head bald. I cant believe it, said the actress, well known for her curly brunette locks.      
	The Monsters Ball actress plays a woman who shaves her head after her hair start to fall out, leading her to deal with peoples perceptions of herself.       
	I still struggle with this hair issue, she remarked while pointing out that her character is forced to look at what beauty is, and it comes from inside.Im going to get the lesson on film, and hopefully other women will get it, too.     
	Gun roses    
	 Columbia, South Carolina (AP): Police in South Carolina are giving out roses on Valentines Day. All you have to do is turn in a gun. Authorities are running the Guns for Roses programme on Saturday at two locations in the central part of the state. Anyone who turns in a gun gets a free rose and an electronics store gift card. A handgun gets a $100 gift card, while a rifle or shotgun nets a $50 gift card. The police says there has already been a great turnout at one Columbia location                                                                                                                                                                              
